    <discussion>Sesuvium maritimum is often overlooked in coastal environments, perhaps due to the
        small size of some individuals, particularly in the northern portions of its distribution.
        Nonetheless, this species appears to be infrequent (and possibly in decline) in coastal
        environments of northern states (e.g., Delaware, Maryland, New Jersey, and New York), where
        development of the coast has impacted sensitive environments. This species is also present
        in Kansas and Oklahoma but its distribution in those states is currently not well
        known.</discussion>
    <discussion>The name Sesuvium sessile Persoon has been misapplied to this species.</discussion>
